# Berreman

## Purpose

Gates that exercise the Berreman F# numerical optics solver
under `Berreman/`. They cover the `Berreman.slnx` solution build
and the `BerremanTests` F# unit-test project (`BerremanTests.fsproj`).
Build runs via `dotnet build`; tests via `dotnet test`. No
Android, no UI smoke harness, no A/V flow -- the project is pure
numerical / analytics code with `xunit`-style F# tests.

## When to add a gate here

Add a gate here when the new check exercises Berreman or one of
its sibling projects under `Berreman/` (`BerremanModelGenerator`,
`BerremanRunner`, `OpticalModel`, `OpticalProperties`,
`Analytics`). Use a descriptive single-word stem (`build`,
`unit-tests`, `integration-tests`, ...) -- the project does not
have multiple long-lived sub-areas that warrant a prefix yet.
Gates that target a different sub-project unrelated to the
optics solver belong in their own `<group>/` subfolder with its
own `.gates-md`.
